Pre-requisites:
truecrypt
fuse
sshfs
rsync

Configuration pre-requisites:
The user that the scripts run under must have sudo priviledges to run the TrueCrypt binary as root.
The user_allow_other option must be uncommented in /etc/fuse.conf

Installation:
1. Create a truecrypt volume with no password and a keyfile on the remote machine.
2. Copy the config-template file to ~/.sobr/config .  It can be copied elsewhere if you run sobr with the -c option.
3. Fill out the required variables in the config file.
4. Set up passwordless SSH access to the remote machine.
5. Install the sobr.sh, functions.sh, and default-vars files in a directory of your choosing.  They must reside in the same directory.

